The paper deals with moment generating functions of wireless fading distributions, which are commonly studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), communication systems (cs.COMM), and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also presents analytical and numerical results, which are often studied in the fields of signal processing (cs.SI) and applied mathematics (cs.MA).
